    content:
      'Consider the complex numbers\n$u = 1 + 2 {\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}$ and\n$v = 2 + {\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}$.\n\n- Given that $\\dfrac{1}{u} + \\dfrac{1}{v} = \\dfrac{6\\sqrt{2}}{w}$,\nexpress $w$ in the form\n$a + b {\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}$ where\n$a,b \\in \\mathbb{R}$.  <span class="marks">[4]</span>\n\n- Find $w^\\ast$ and express it in the form\n$re^{{\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}\\theta}$. <span class="marks">[3]</span>\n\n',
    markScheme:
      "\n- Substituting $u = 1+2{\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}$ and\n$v = 2+{\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}$ in the given equation,\nwe have\n\n  $$\n  \\begin{aligned}\n  \\hspace{2.1em} \\dfrac{6\\sqrt{2}}{w} &= \\dfrac{1}{u} + \\dfrac{1}{v} \\\\[6pt]\n  &=  \\dfrac{1}{1 + 2 {\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}} + \\dfrac{1}{2 + {\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}} \\\\[6pt]\n  &=  \\dfrac{1}{1 + 2 {\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}}\\cdot\\dfrac{1 - 2 {\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}}{1 - 2 {\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}} + \\dfrac{1}{2 + {\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}}\\cdot\\dfrac{2 - {\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}}{2 - {\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}} \\\\[6pt]\n  &= \\dfrac{1 - 2 {\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}}{5} + \\dfrac{2 - {\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}}{5} \\\\[6pt]\n  &= \\dfrac{3 - 3 {\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}}{5} \\qref{(1)} \\end{aligned}\n  $$\n\n  Hence, solving the equation $(1)$ for $w$, we get\n\n  $$\n  \\begin{aligned}\n  w &= \\dfrac{30\\sqrt{2}}{3 - 3{\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}} \\\\[5pt]\n  &= \\dfrac{10\\sqrt{2}}{1 - {\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}}\\cdot\\dfrac{1 + {\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}}{1 + {\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}} \\\\[5pt]\n  &= \\dfrac{10\\sqrt{2}\\hspace{0.05em}(1 + {\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu})}{2} \\\\[11pt]\n  &= 5\\sqrt{2}\\hspace{0.05em}(1 + {\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}) \\\\[14pt]\n  &\\answer{= 5\\sqrt{2} + 5\\sqrt{2}{\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}} \\hspace{4em}\\end{aligned}\n  $$\n\n- The conjugate of $w$ is\n\n  $$\n  \\begin{aligned}\n  \\hspace{5.1em} w^\\ast &= 5\\sqrt{2} - 5\\sqrt{2}{\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}\\\\[8pt]\n  &= 10\\bigg[\\dfrac{\\sqrt{2}}{2} - \\dfrac{\\sqrt{2}}{2}{\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}\\bigg] \\\\[6pt]\n  &= 10\\left[\\cos\\left(\\dfrac{\\pi}{4}\\right) - {\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}\\sin\\left(\\dfrac{\\pi}{4}\\right)\\right] \\\\[9pt]\n  &= 10\\left[\\cos\\left(-\\dfrac{\\pi}{4}\\right) + {\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}\\sin\\left(-\\dfrac{\\pi}{4}\\right)\\right] \\\\[12pt]\n  &\\answer{= 10\\hspace{0.05em}e^{-{\\mathrm{\\hspace{0.05em}i}\\mkern 1mu}\\frac{\\pi}{4}}} \\hspace{3em} [\\text{by Euler's formula}]\\end{aligned}\n  $$\n\n",
