      '\n- Prove that $\\dfrac{5}{x^2} = \\dfrac{5}{x(x-2)}-\\dfrac{10}{x^2(x-2)}$. <span class="marks">[3]</span>\n\n- Determine the set of numbers $x$ for which the proof in part (a) is valid. <span class="marks">[2]</span>\n\n\n\n$$\n\n$$\n',
