    content:
      'The following diagram shows the graph of $y = f(x)$. The graph has a\nhorizontal asymptote at $y = -2$. The graph crosses the $x$-axis at\n$x = -1$ and $x = 1$, and the $y$-axis at $y = 2$.\n![SkillUpp Image](https://assets.revisionvillage.com/public/question/f3c6f7c6-fc9b-4711-b409-c94ab4639150/images/3b7dba3d-a488-40f3-a3a5-3ab8beeed143/78cc89164062caf98085797a78fe4274df588839.svg)\n\n\nOn the following set of axes, sketch the graph of $y = [f(x)]^2-2$,\nclearly showing any asymptotes with their equations and the coordinates\nof any local maxima or minima.\n![SkillUpp Image](https://assets.revisionvillage.com/public/question/f3c6f7c6-fc9b-4711-b409-c94ab4639150/images/4c7d1f64-c18e-4b39-a199-46ba4b55ea8d/43ee184d47f5a2762efb07289d20445bdfc20e52.svg)\n\n',
